cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL 

This paper is about recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework involves training a model selector, which can be seen as a form of meta-learning, and thus falls under the sub-field of meta-learning (cs.SI). Finally, the experiments involve evaluating the framework's performance in terms of AUC and LogLoss, which are commonly used evaluation metrics in natural language processing (cs.CL).
